
[1]pyrorthite

   PYRORTHITE, n. A mineral little known, resembling orthite, but very
   different from it, for it burns in the flame of the blowpipe like
   charcoal; whereas orthite melts. Pyrorthite is in black plates, thin
   and almost parallel.
